How to print USER-JSON data in React table using an External API?

Given a API(https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users);

using the above API we have write our code in react using with latest hooks(useState, useEffect)

Answer : 

import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

function PersonData() {
  const [data, setData] = useState([]);

  const fetchData = () => {
    fetch(`https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users`)
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((actualdata) => {
        setData(actualdata);
        console.log(actualdata);
      });
  };
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchData();
  }, []);

  return (
    <>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th>Id</th>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Username</th>
          <th>E-mail</th>
          <th>Company</th>
          <th>Phone</th>
          <th>City</th>
          <th>Zipcode</th>
          <th>Website</th>
        </tr>
        {data.map((item, index) => (
          <tr key={index}>
            <td>{item.id}</td>
            <td>{item.name}</td>
            <td>{item.username}</td>
            <td>{item.email}</td>
            <td>{item.company.name}</td>
            <td>{item.phone}</td>
            <td>{item.address.city}</td>
            <td>{item.address.zipcode}</td>
            <td>{item.website}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </>
  );
}

export default PersonData;
Write a code for Auto-Incrementing app using React.js?

1.There are several ways they ask me to implement initial draft was i have developed Increment and Decerement using buttons where we have to manually increment and decrement using buttons with a conditiion on decrementing less than 0 it should not exceed to -ve values.
2.In 2nd pattern they ask me to implement the auto-increment using useEffect write a method and a condition after 15 value should stop priniting values(here i have used SetInterval and ClearInterval)

1.
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

function AutoIncrementCounter() {
  const [counter, setCounter] = useState(0);

  useEffect(() => {
    // This function will be called after the component is mounted
    const intervalId = setInterval(() => {
      setCounter((prevCounter) => prevCounter + 1);
    }, 1000);

    // This function will be called when the component is unmounted
    return () => clearInterval(intervalId);
  }, []); // The empty dependency array ensures that the effect runs only once, similar to componentDidMount

  return (
    <div>
      <p>Counter: {counter}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
